{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Continuous auto-deploy: the running Gerrit environment reflects `main` without manual deploy or restart\n\n## Why\nLanding a change on `main` does NOT update the running environment: the review-bot container's code,\n`replication.config`, and g2p config need a MANUAL deploy (SSM / setup-*.sh) + sometimes a restart.\nThis drifts + toils (S2's merge-review code landed but the running bot is pre-S2; the S3 replication\nfix was hand-applied). The environment must AUTO-REFLECT `main` — without ever destabilising the\nLIVE, FAIL-CLOSED gate (no LLM-Review vote ⇒ no submit; a bad deploy could freeze all submissions).\n\n## What\n- **Trigger (RESOLVED): on-box systemd timer** `rebar-autodeploy.timer` (2-min) → `.service` oneshot\n  running `infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh`. Chosen over a GitHub-Actions→SSM `deploy.yml` because it adds\n  NO GitHub→AWS trust surface (no OIDC/`ssm:SendCommand` grant that would make the GH runner a\n  lateral-movement path); the box already reads the PUBLIC mirror read-only + has an instance role.\n- **Loop:** `flock -n` guard; fetch `origin/main`; no-op when `== deployed-sha`\n  (`/var/lib/rebar/deployed-sha`, initialised to current HEAD on first run WITHOUT deploying, written\n  atomically only on success). Deploy ONLY the mirror `main` tip (Verified-by-construction: it only\n  advances via Gerrit submit). Change-detect per component via `git diff --name-only\n  deployed-sha..origin/main` ∩ a path manifest (review-bot: src/rebar/**, Dockerfile.reviewbot,\n  pyproject, docker-compose; replication: replication.config; g2p: ini + materialize script).\n- **Apply only what changed:** review-bot → tag current image `:prev`, `docker compose up -d --build\n  review-bot`; replication/g2p → re-materialise (autoReload / g2p copy). `refs/meta/config` is OUT of\n  v1 (needs an operator-only admin key): a change is DETECTED + signalled, never auto-applied.\n\n## Stability — live-pipeline safety (load-bearing)\n1. **Bounded blast radius:** never touch the `gerrit` container (explicit `review-bot` service target\n   + a post-deploy assert the gerrit container id is unchanged); never modify `refs/meta/config` (gate\n   labels/rules/ACLs). No Gerrit restart — only the bot container restarts, only on a code change.\n2. **In-flight reviews delayed, not lost:** a restart drops in-flight webhooks, but the existing\n   reconciler-backfill re-reviews them; the post-deploy health check confirms the reconciler is live.\n3. **Self-heal, never freeze the gate:** after `up -d --build`, an END-TO-END health check (30s\n   timeout — bot can actually review, not just process-up) gates success; on failure → immediate\n   rollback to `:prev` + `up -d`; deployed-sha NOT advanced. Max frozen window = the health timeout.\n4. **Failure handling = capped exponential backoff, NOT hard-disable** (mature-OSS consensus: Flux\n   retryInterval/backoff; Argo CD retry backoff duration/factor/maxDuration; k8s controller-runtime\n   ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter 5ms→1000s; systemd v254 RestartSteps/RestartMaxDelaySec):\n   - rollback keeps last-known-good RUNNING; retry the deploy with backoff base 60s, factor 2, cap\n     15m — never auto-disable the loop (a hard-disable strands the env stale until a human acts).\n   - **SHA-keyed reset (Argo CD's rule):** persist last-attempted-SHA + failure count; a NEW\n     `origin/main` tip RESETS the backoff to base (a fix-forward deploys promptly); a known-bad SHA is\n     not re-attempted faster than the cap (no thrash) and is never permanently blacklisted.\n   - **Outer storm guard:** systemd `StartLimitIntervalSec`/`StartLimitBurst` on the RUNNING bot\n     service catches a crash-looping container (→ failed, needs `reset-failed`) — reserved for the\n     pathological case, NOT the primary retry path.\n5. **Config validated before it touches Gerrit:** parse-check replication/g2p config pre-apply; a\n   malformed config is skipped (prior retained) + alarmed. (Belt-and-suspenders to AC below.)\n\n## Defense-in-depth: a CI gate that rejects malformed config (so it never reaches `main`)\n`make config-check` — parse-validate every infra config: `git config -f {replication,project}.config\n--list`; python configparser on the g2p ini template; `docker compose config -q`; `bash -n` on\n`infra/**/*.sh`. Wired into `test.yml` (⇒ runs in `gerrit-verify` ⇒ the `Verified` gate), so a\nmalformed config FAILS CI and can NEVER land on `main` — the auto-deploy never encounters one at\nruntime (the runtime pre-apply check in Stability §5 is the belt-and-suspenders for a direct box edit).\n\n## Observability + back-out\nStructured deploy log (from→to SHA + components) + `rebar/host:deploy_errors` (host-probe grep of an\n`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR` marker, mirroring voter_errors) + a CloudWatch alarm w/ SNS action; the\nbackoff/failure state is alarmed. Back-out: `systemctl disable --now rebar-autodeploy.timer`; the\nmanual path (compose-up.sh / setup-*.sh) is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\nDeploy orchestrator + systemd units + stability guards + the CI config-check + observability/back-out\non the existing compose stack. Reuses the idempotent setup/materialise appliers. refs/meta/config\nauto-apply deferred (detect + signal). No change to gate semantics (S1/S2) or the 88ab flow.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A post-gate `main` change auto-reflects on the box (no manual action) ≤ 5 min; latency\n      live-measured. Idempotent: a no-change run is a no-op; a change re-applies ONLY the changed\n      component(s) — verified for review-bot code, replication.config, g2p separately\n- [ ] review-bot rebuilt/restarted ONLY on a source-set change (docs-only change ⇒ no rebuild); after\n      a code change the running bot reflects it end-to-end (a merge change gets the S2 merge tag)\n- [ ] Blast radius: the `gerrit` container is provably untouched; `refs/meta/config` never\n      auto-modified; no Gerrit restart. project.config changes are detected + signalled, not attempted\n- [ ] Self-heal: a deliberately-broken bot image FAILS the health check ⇒ rollback to `:prev` (gate\n      restored), deployed-sha not advanced (proven live)\n- [ ] Failure backoff: repeated failure uses capped exponential backoff (base 60s→cap 15m), keeps\n      last-known-good running, and a NEW `main` SHA resets the backoff (fix-forward deploys promptly);\n      the loop never auto-disables; the systemd StartLimit storm-guard is in place\n- [ ] CI config-gate: `make config-check` runs in `test.yml`/`gerrit-verify` and FAILS on a\n      deliberately-malformed config (proven) — a malformed config cannot reach `main`\n- [ ] flock serializes overlapping fires; deploy log + `deploy_errors` metric + alarm applied;\n      back-out (disable timer) tested; manual path still works; live end-to-end auto-deploy verified\n\n## Box-adaptation of the deploy mechanism (grounded in live box i-00880b2c7f13527c5)\n\nThe v1-v4 plan above assumed the compose build context is a **git checkout** it could\n`git checkout <sha>` in place (`DEPLOY_REPO=/opt/rebar/src`). Live inspection (SSM) shows the\nbox deploys by **copy, not git**, so the mechanism is adapted (semantics/guarantees below are\nUNCHANGED — only *how* source reaches the build context changes):\n\n- **Observed box facts:** `/opt/rebar` is a plain **copy** of the repo root (no `.git`; uid 502;\n  a `.deployed_ref` marker file), and it is the compose build `context:` for BOTH services. The\n  real compose working dir is `/opt/rebar/infra/compose` (services `gerrit`, `review-bot`).\n  systemd 252. review-bot health = `http://localhost:8000/health` → `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`. The ONLY\n  runtime state living under `/opt/rebar` is `infra/compose/.env` (SSM-sourced secrets, git-ignored,\n  0600, regenerated by `fetch-secrets.sh`). Docker state lives OUTSIDE `/opt/rebar` — named volumes\n  (`gerrit_git`/`gerrit_index`/…) + bind mounts under `/var/gerrit/*` — so a source resync cannot\n  touch it.\n\n- **Adapted mechanism:**\n  1. autodeploy maintains its OWN **git mirror clone** at `MIRROR_DIR=/var/lib/rebar/mirror` (a clone\n     of the PUBLIC GitHub mirror, read-only). ALL git operations — fetch, `rev-parse`, the\n     `git diff --name-only deployed..target` component change-detection, checkout of the target — run\n     THERE (git-based change-detection is preserved verbatim; only its location moves off `/opt/rebar`).\n  2. **Source sync = `rsync -a --delete $MIRROR_DIR/ /opt/rebar/`** with hard excludes that protect\n     runtime state: `--exclude '/.git'`, `--exclude 'infra/compose/.env'`, `--exclude '/.deployed_ref'`\n     (plus the git-ignored dev-state set `.venv .terraform .serena .claude .tickets-tracker` for safety).\n     `.env` and Docker volumes are therefore never deleted or overwritten. Ownership kept 502:502.\n  3. Compose build/up runs in `/opt/rebar/infra/compose` on the `review-bot` service only.\n  4. `deployed-sha` state + backoff + first-run-adopt semantics are unchanged; on first run the marker\n     is seeded from `/opt/rebar/.deployed_ref` if present (else the current mirror tip), still WITHOUT\n     deploying.\n\n- **systemd unit fix:** script path `/opt/rebar/infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh` (NOT `/opt/rebar/src/…`),\n  `DEPLOY_REPO=/opt/rebar`, add `MIRROR_DIR=/var/lib/rebar/mirror`. Blast-radius / self-heal / rollback /\n  SHA-keyed backoff / config-check-before-apply / flock — ALL unchanged.\n\n### Additional acceptance criteria (box-adaptation)\n- [ ] autodeploy syncs source into the copy-based `/opt/rebar` via a self-maintained mirror clone +\n      rsync (NO in-place git checkout of the build context), and the resync provably preserves\n      `infra/compose/.env` (secrets intact) and never touches the Docker volumes / `gerrit` container\n- [ ] the corrected systemd unit points at the real on-box paths and the manual dry-run applies a real\n      `main` advance end-to-end on the box (review-bot rebuilt from the synced source, health OK)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783104964420732001,"uuid":"ae8482ed-89a1-43da-88dc-9db2899968d4"}